{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877948014,"sessionID":"ses_2856eb0b4ffeWi1fdhVo2dAcTE","part":{"id":"prt_d7a930240001MypNayWQ301cq3","messageID":"msg_d7a92f165001vFQ2RZ2RXVz8bW","sessionID":"ses_2856eb0b4ffeWi1fdhVo2dAcTE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-7499e3afff564808813a55bcff243977","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — MetadataService 与数据模型\n2: \n3: AR: AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n4: Module: cmd/cli\n5: Language: Python\n6: Size: M\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Requirement: MetadataService 初始化\n11: \n12: The system SHALL provide `MetadataService` as a service class for metadata file operations.\n13: \n14: ### Scenario: 默认构造\n15: \n16: - **GIVEN** `MetadataService` is instantiated\n17: - **WHEN** no arguments are provided\n18: - **THEN** `verbose` SHALL default to `False`\n19: \n20: ### Scenario: verbose 参数传入\n21: \n22: - **GIVEN** `MetadataService(verbose=True)` is instantiated\n23: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n24: - **THEN** `self.verbose` SHALL be `True`\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ## Requirement: AgentMetadata 数据模型 (Pydantic BaseModel)\n29: \n30: The system SHALL define `AgentMetadata` as a Pydantic `BaseModel` with field validators for language, build_mode, and port.\n31: \n32: ### Scenario: 必填字段验证\n33: \n34: - **GIVEN** `AgentMetadata` is instantiated\n35: - **WHEN** `agent_name` or `entrypoint` is not provided\n36: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` (fields marked with `Field(..., description=...)` are required)\n37: \n38: ### Scenario: 可选字段默认值\n39: \n40: - **GIVEN** `AgentMetadata` is instantiated without optional fields\n41: - **WHEN** defaults are applied\n42: - **THEN** the following defaults SHALL be used:\n43:   - `description`: `\"\"`\n44:   - `language`: `\"python\"`\n45:   - `port`: `8080`\n46:   - `build_mode`: `\"local\"`\n47:   - `region`: `\"\"`\n48:   - `version`: `\"\"`\n49:   - `image`: `default_factory=dict` (empty dict)\n50:   - `auth`: `default_factory=dict` (empty dict)\n51:   - `requirements_file`: `\"requirements.txt\"`\n52:   - `registry_url`: `\"\"`\n53:   - `registry_username`: `\"\"`\n54:   - `registry_password`: `\"\"`\n55:   - `agent_endpoint`: `\"\"`\n56:   - `workload_manager_url`: `\"\"`\n57:   - `router_url`: `\"\"`\n58:   - `readiness_probe_path`: `\"\"`\n59:   - `readiness_probe_port`: `8080`\n60:   - `agent_id`: `\"\"`\n61:   - `session_id`: `\"\"`\n62:   - `k8s_deployment`: `default_factory=dict` (empty dict)\n63: \n64: ### Scenario: language 字段验证 — 大写转换\n65: \n66: - **GIVEN** `AgentMetadata` receives `language=\"Python\"` or `\"PYTHON\"`\n67: - **WHEN** the field validator runs\n68: - **THEN** the value SHALL be lowercased to `\"python\"` and accepted\n69: \n70: ### Scenario: language 字段验证 — 非允许值拒绝\n71: \n72: - **GIVEN** `AgentMetadata` receives `language=\"go\"` or `\"ruby\"`\n73: - **WHEN** the field validator runs\n74: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"language must be one of ['python', 'java']\")`\n75: \n76: ### Scenario: build_mode 字段验证 — 大写转换\n77: \n78: - **GIVEN** `AgentMetadata` receives `build_mode=\"Local\"` or `\"LOCAL\"`\n79: - **WHEN** the field validator runs\n80: - **THEN** the value SHALL be lowercased to `\"local\"` and accepted\n81: \n82: ### Scenario: build_mode 字段验证 — 非允许值拒绝\n83: \n84: - **GIVEN** `AgentMetadata` receives `build_mode=\"docker\"` or `\"remote\"`\n85: - **WHEN** the field validator runs\n86: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"build_mode must be one of ['local', 'cloud']\")`\n87: \n88: ### Scenario: port 字段验证 — 有效范围\n89: \n90: - **GIVEN** `AgentMetadata` receives `port=8080` or `port=1` or `port=65535`\n91: - **WHEN** the field validator runs\n92: - **THEN** the value SHALL be accepted\n93: \n94: ### Scenario: port 字段验证 — 超出范围拒绝\n95: \n96: - **GIVEN** `AgentMetadata` receives `port=0` or `port=65536` or `port=-1`\n97: - **WHEN** the field validator runs\n98: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"port must be between 1 and 65535\")`\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## Requirement: MetadataService.load_metadata\n103: \n104: The system SHALL load metadata from YAML files with primary filename `agent_metadata.yaml` and fallback order: `agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml`.\n105: \n106: ### Scenario: 主文件存在\n107: \n108: - **GIVEN** `{workspace_path}/agent_metadata.yaml` exists\n109: - **WHEN** `load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n110: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n111:   - Read the file content with `yaml.safe_load`\n112:   - Construct `AgentMetadata(**data)` from parsed YAML\n113:   - Return the `AgentMetadata` instance\n114: \n115: ### Scenario: 主文件不存在 — 回退到 agent.yaml\n116: \n117: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does NOT exist but `agent.yaml` exists\n118: - **WHEN** `load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n119: - **THEN** the system SHALL load from `agent.yaml` and return `AgentMetadata`\n120: \n121: ### Scenario: 主和次级文件不存在 — 回退到 metadata.yaml\n122: \n123: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` and `agent.yaml` do NOT exist but `metadata.yaml` exists\n124: - **WHEN** `load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n125: - **THEN** the system SHALL load from `metadata.yaml` and return `AgentMetadata`\n126: \n127: ### Scenario: 所有元数据文件不存在\n128: \n129: - **GIVEN** none of `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml` exist in workspace\n130: - **WHEN** `load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n131: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError(\"No metadata file found in workspace: {workspace_path}\")`\n132: \n133: ### Scenario: YAML 内容为空或 null\n134: \n135: - **GIVEN** the metadata file exists but content is empty or YAML parses to `None`\n136: - **WHEN** the file is loaded\n137: - **THEN** the system SHALL treat empty content as `{}` and create `AgentMetadata` with defaults\n138: \n139: ### Scenario: YAML 内容字段类型错误\n140: \n141: - **GIVEN** metadata YAML contains `port: \"not-a-number\"` (invalid type)\n142: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata(**data)` validation runs\n143: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` for the type mismatch\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ## Requirement: MetadataService.save_metadata\n148: \n149: The system SHALL persist metadata to `{workspace_path}/agent_metadata.yaml` using `yaml.dump` with specific formatting options.\n150: \n151: ### Scenario: 保存到主文件路径\n152: \n153: - **GIVEN** `workspace_path` exists and `metadata` is an `AgentMetadata` instance\n154: - **WHEN** `save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n155: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n156:   - Write to `{workspace_path}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n157:   - Return the file `Path` object\n158: \n159: ### Scenario: YAML 输出格式参数\n160: \n161: - **GIVEN** metadata is being saved\n162: - **WHEN** `yaml.dump` is called\n163: - **THEN** the following parameters SHALL be used:\n164:   - `default_flow_style=False` (block format, not inline)\n165:   - `indent=2`\n166:   - `sort_keys=False` (preserve field order)\n167:   - Data from `metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True)` (exclude `None` fields)\n168: \n169: ### Scenario: 空字典字段包含在输出\n170: \n171: - **GIVEN** `image`, `auth`, or `k8s_deployment` fields are empty dicts `{}` (not `None`)\n172: - **WHEN** metadata is saved\n173: - **THEN** empty dicts SHALL be included in YAML output (because `exclude_none=True` only excludes `None`, not empty dicts)\n174: \n175: ### Scenario: None 值字段排除\n176: \n177: - **GIVEN** a field value is `None` (not an empty string or empty dict)\n178: - **WHEN** metadata is saved with `exclude_none=True`\n179: - **THEN** that field SHALL NOT appear in the YAML output\n180: \n181: ---\n182: \n183: ## Requirement: MetadataService.update_metadata (待实现)\n184: \n185: The system SHALL provide `update_metadata` to load existing metadata, apply updates, and save.\n186: \n187: ### Scenario: 更新部分字段\n188: \n189: - **GIVEN** workspace has existing metadata file with `version=\"\"` and `description=\"old\"`\n190: - **WHEN** `update_metadata(workspace_path, {\"version\": \"v1.0.0\", \"description\": \"new desc\"})` is called\n191: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n192:   - Load existing metadata via `load_metadata`\n193:   - Apply the updates dict to metadata fields\n194:   - Save via `save_metadata`\n195:   - Return the updated `AgentMetadata` instance\n196: \n197: ### Scenario: 更新触发验证错误\n198: \n199: - **GIVEN** updates dict contains `{\"language\": \"rust\"}`\n200: - **WHEN** the updated metadata is validated\n201: - **THEN** `AgentMetadata` validator SHALL raise `ValueError` for invalid language\n202: \n203: ---\n204: \n205: ## Requirement: MetadataService.validate_workspace (待实现)\n206: \n207: The system SHALL validate workspace structure based on the language specified in metadata.\n208: \n209: ### Scenario: workspace 路径不存在\n210: \n211: - **GIVEN** `workspace_path` does NOT exist or is NOT a directory\n212: - **WHEN** `validate_workspace(workspace_path)` is called\n213: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating path does not exist or is not a directory\n214: \n215: ### Scenario: Python workspace 验证成功\n216: \n217: - **GIVEN** metadata `language == \"python\"` and workspace contains at least one `.py` file\n218: - **WHEN** `_validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` runs\n219: - **THEN** the system SHALL return without raising an error\n220: \n221: ### Scenario: Python workspace 无 Python 文件\n222: \n223: - **GIVEN** metadata `language == \"python\"` and workspace has NO `.py` files\n224: - **WHEN** `_validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` runs\n225: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n226: \n227: ### Scenario: Java workspace 验证成功\n228: \n229: - **GIVEN** metadata `language == \"java\"` and workspace contains `pom.xml`\n230: - **WHEN** `_validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` runs\n231: - **THEN** the system SHALL return without raising an error\n232: \n233: ### Scenario: Java workspace 无 pom.xml\n234: \n235: - **GIVEN** metadata `language == \"java\"` and workspace has NO `pom.xml`\n236: - **WHEN** `_validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` runs\n237: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"pom.xml not found in workspace\")`\n238: \n239: ---\n240: \n241: ## Requirement: MetadataOptions 数据类 (pack_models.py)\n242: \n243: The system SHALL define `MetadataOptions` as a dataclass for CLI option mapping.\n244: \n245: ### Scenario: 默认值设置\n246: \n247: - **GIVEN** `MetadataOptions` is instantiated without arguments\n248: - **WHEN** defaults are applied\n249: - **THEN** the following defaults SHALL be used:\n250:   - `agent_name`: `None`\n251:   - `language`: `\"python\"`\n252:   - `entrypoint`: `None`\n253:   - `port`: `8080`\n254:   - `build_mode`: `\"local\"`\n255:   - `requirements_file`: `None`\n256:   - `description`: `None`\n257:   - `workload_manager_url`: `\"\"`\n258:   - `router_url`: `\"\"`\n259:   - `readiness_probe_path`: `\"\"`\n260:   - `readiness_probe_port`: `8080`\n261:   - `registry_url`: `\"\"`\n262:   - `registry_username`: `\"\"`\n263:   - `registry_password`: `\"\"`\n264:   - `agent_endpoint`: `\"\"`\n265: \n266: ### Scenario: from_options 工厂方法 — 正常输入\n267: \n268: - **GIVEN** `options = {\"agent_name\": \"my-agent\", \"language\": \"java\", \"port\": 9090}`\n269: - **WHEN** `MetadataOptions.from_options(options)` is called\n270: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n271:   - Filter out entries where value is `None`\n272:   - Create `MetadataOptions` instance with remaining values\n273:   - Return instance with `agent_name=\"my-agent\"`, `language=\"java\"`, `port=9090`\n274: \n275: ### Scenario: from_options 工厂方法 — 过滤 None 值\n276: \n277: - **GIVEN** `options = {\"agent_name\": None, \"language\": \"python\", \"entrypoint\": None}`\n278: - **WHEN** `MetadataOptions.from_options(options)` is called\n279: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n280:   - Filter out `\"agent_name\"` and `\"entrypoint\"` because their values are `None`\n281:   - Return instance using defaults for filtered fields\n282: \n283: ### Scenario: from_options 工厂方法 — 未知键忽略\n284: \n285: - **GIVEN** `options = {\"agent_name\": \"test\", \"unknown_field\": \"value\"}`\n286: - **WHEN** `MetadataOptions.from_options(options)` is called\n287: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n288:   - Pass only matching dataclass fields to constructor\n289:   - Ignore `unknown_field` or raise error depending on implementation\n290: \n291: ---\n292: \n293: ## Requirement: Metadata 文件格式规范\n294: \n295: The system SHALL use YAML format with specific naming and formatting conventions.\n296: \n297: ### Scenario: 主文件名 agent_metadata.yaml\n298: \n299: - **GIVEN** metadata is saved\n300: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` runs\n301: - **THEN** the primary filename SHALL be `agent_metadata.yaml` (not `agentcube.yaml`)\n302: \n303: ### Scenario: 加载文件名优先级\n304: \n305: - **GIVEN** multiple metadata files may exist\n306: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` searches for files\n307: - **THEN** the priority order SHALL be:\n308:   1. `agent_metadata.yaml` (primary)\n309:   2. `agent.yaml` (fallback)\n310:   3. `metadata.yaml` (secondary fallback)\n311: \n312: ---\n313: \n314: ## Requirement: Pydantic validator 使用 field_validator\n315: \n316: The system SHALL use Pydantic v2 `field_validator` decorator for field validation.\n317: \n318: ### Scenario: validator 方法签名\n319: \n320: - **GIVEN** a field validator is defined\n321: - **WHEN** using `@field_validator(\"language\")`\n322: - **THEN** the validator method SHALL be a `@classmethod` and receive `v: str` (the field value)\n323: \n324: ### Scenario: validator 返回转换值\n325: \n326: - **GIVEN** `language` validator lowercases the input\n327: - **WHEN** input is `\"Python\"`\n328: - **THEN** validator SHALL return `\"python\"` (the transformed value)\n329: \n330: ---\n331: \n332: ## Implementation Files\n333: \n334: | File | Purpose |\n335: |------|---------|\n336: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `AgentMetadata` model, `MetadataService` class |\n337: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n338: \n339: ---\n340: \n341: ## Dependencies\n342: \n343: | Package | Purpose |\n344: |---------|---------|\n345: | `pydantic>=2.0.0` | `BaseModel`, `Field`, `field_validator` |\n346: | `pyyaml>=6.0` | `yaml.safe_load`, `yaml.dump` |\n347: | `pathlib` | `Path` for file operations |\n348: \n349: ---\n350: \n351: ## Validation Checklist\n352: \n353: - [ ] `AgentMetadata` defined as Pydantic `BaseModel`\n354: - [ ] Required fields: `agent_name`, `entrypoint` (use `Field(...)`)\n355: - [ ] Optional fields have correct defaults (`\"\"`, `default_factory=dict`, etc.)\n356: - [ ] `validate_language` accepts `python`/`java`, lowercases input, rejects others\n357: - [ ] `validate_build_mode` accepts `local`/`cloud`, lowercases input, rejects others\n358: - [ ] `validate_port` accepts `1..65535`, rejects out-of-range\n359: - [ ] `MetadataService.__init__` accepts `verbose` parameter\n360: - [ ] `load_metadata` checks `agent_metadata.yaml` first, then `agent.yaml`, then `metadata.yaml`\n361: - [ ] `load_metadata` raises `FileNotFoundError` when no file found\n362: - [ ] `load_metadata` handles empty YAML as `{}` with defaults\n363: - [ ] `save_metadata` writes to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n364: - [ ] `save_metadata` uses `yaml.dump(default_flow_style=False, indent=2, sort_keys=False)`\n365: - [ ] `save_metadata` uses `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n366: - [ ] `save_metadata` returns `Path` to saved file\n367: - [ ] `MetadataOptions` dataclass with correct fields and defaults\n368: - [ ] `MetadataOptions.from_options` filters `None` values from input dict\n\n(End of file - total 368 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — MetadataService 与数据模型\n\nAR: AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\nModule: cmd/cli\nLanguage: Python\nSize: M\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: MetadataService 初始化\n\nThe system SHALL provide `MetadataService` as a service class for metadata file operations.\n\n### Scenario: 默认构造\n\n- **GIVEN** `MetadataService` is instantiated\n- **WHEN** no arguments are provided\n- **THEN** `verbose` SHALL default to `False`\n\n### Scenario: verbose 参数传入","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775877947996,"end":1775877948011}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775877948036,"sessionID":"ses_2856eb0b4ffeWi1fdhVo2dAcTE","part":{"id":"prt_d7a93026d001jak88qzYuiefNS","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a92f165001vFQ2RZ2RXVz8bW","sessionID":"ses_2856eb0b4ffeWi1fdhVo2dAcTE","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":38786,"input":6714,"output":73,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":31999}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775877954037,"sessionID":"ses_2856eb0b4ffeWi1fdhVo2dAcTE","part":{"id":"prt_d7a9319f3001rLFJCYzgxrmp4E","messageID":"msg_d7a93029b001W560koVX7tP16u","sessionID":"ses_2856eb0b4ffeWi1fdhVo2dAcTE","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878037626,"sessionID":"ses_2856eb0b4ffeWi1fdhVo2dAcTE","part":{"id":"prt_d7a946022001gOdfPGjY7CKEpo","messageID":"msg_d7a93029b001W560koVX7tP16u","sessionID":"ses_2856eb0b4ffeWi1fdhVo2dAcTE","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-8e7883962a864f968bcc126255387336","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n\nAR: AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\nModule: cmd/cli\nLanguage: Python\nSize: M\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement K8s/AgentCube provider integration for deploying AI agents as either standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + Service) or AgentCube Custom Resources (AgentRuntime CR), enabling lifecycle management through CLI commands.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider initialization\n\nThe system SHALL construct `KubernetesProvider` with configurable namespace, kubeconfig path, and verbose logging.\n\n#### Scenario: Default namespace and kubeconfig\n\n- **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider` is instantiated without arguments\n- **WHEN** the constructor runs\n- **THEN** `namespace` SHALL default to `\"default\"`, `kubeconfig` SHALL default to `None` (using in-cluster or default kubeconfig), and `verbose` SHALL default to `False`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom kubeconfig path\n\n- **GIVEN** a custom kubeconfig file path is provided\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.__init__(kubeconfig=\"/path/to/config\")` runs\n- **THEN** the client SHALL load configuration from the specified file via `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)`\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace auto-creation\n\n- **GIVEN** the specified namespace does not exist in the cluster\n- **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` is called\n- **THEN** the provider SHALL create the namespace with `kubernetes.client.V1Namespace(metadata=V1ObjectMeta(name=namespace))` and log the creation\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — deploy agent\n\nThe system SHALL create or patch a `Deployment` and a `NodePort` `Service` for the agent, returning deployment info.\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment creation\n\n- **GIVEN** `deploy_agent(agent_name, image_url, port, entrypoint=None, replicas=1, node_port=None, env_vars=None)` is called\n- **WHEN** resources are applied\n- **THEN** the provider SHALL:\n  - Call `_create_deployment` with sanitized name (DNS-compliant: lowercase, alphanumeric, hyphens, max 63 chars)\n  - Call `_create_service` with the same sanitized name\n  - Ensure namespace exists via `_ensure_namespace`\n  - Return dict with `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, `service_url`\n\n#### Scenario: NodePort assignment\n\n- **GIVEN** `node_port` is specified in range 30000-32767\n- **WHEN** `_create_service` creates the Service\n- **THEN** the Service spec SHALL set `type: NodePort` with `nodePort: {node_port}` and `port: {port}` targeting the container port\n- **AND** `service_url` SHALL be `http://localhost:{node_port}`\n\n#### Scenario: Auto NodePort\n\n- **GIVEN** `node_port` is `None`\n- **WHEN** the Service is created\n- **THEN** Kubernetes SHALL assign a random NodePort in the valid range\n- **AND** the provider SHALL retrieve the assigned port from the Service status\n\n#### Scenario: Entrypoint override\n\n- **GIVEN** `entrypoint` is provided\n- **WHEN** the Deployment container spec is constructed\n- **THEN** `command` SHALL be set to the entrypoint command (parsed as list if string)\n\n#### Scenario: Environment variables injection\n\n- **GIVEN** `env_vars` dict is provided\n- **WHEN** the Deployment container spec is constructed\n- **THEN** each key-value pair SHALL be added as `V1EnvVar(name=key, value=value)`\n\n#### Scenario: Sanitize name\n\n- **GIVEN** an agent name with special characters or uppercase\n- **WHEN** `_sanitize_name(name)` runs\n- **THEN** the result SHALL be: lowercase, replace underscores and spaces with hyphens, strip non-alphanumeric/hyphen chars, truncate to 63 chars, strip leading/trailing hyphens\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — wait for deployment ready\n\nThe system SHALL poll deployment status until all replicas are ready or timeout.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful rollout\n\n- **GIVEN** a Deployment with `replicas=3`\n- **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name, timeout=120)` is called\n- **THEN** the provider SHALL poll `read_namespaced_deployment_status` until `status.ready_replicas == replicas` and log progress\n- **AND** return when ready within timeout\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout failure\n\n- **GIVEN** deployment pods fail to become ready\n- **WHEN** `timeout` seconds elapse without all replicas ready\n- **THEN** the provider SHALL raise `TimeoutError(f\"Deployment {name} not ready after {timeout} seconds\")`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — get agent status\n\nThe system SHALL retrieve deployment and service status for the agent.\n\n#### Scenario: Status retrieval\n\n- **GIVEN** an agent was deployed via `deploy_agent`\n- **WHEN** `get_agent_status(agent_name)` is called\n- **THEN** the provider SHALL:\n  - Read Deployment status (name, namespace, replicas, ready_replicas, available_replicas)\n  - Read Service status (name, port, node_port)\n  - Return dict with `status` (`\"running\"` if ready, `\"pending\"` if not ready, `\"not_found\"` if missing)\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment not found\n\n- **GIVEN** no Deployment exists for `agent_name`\n- **WHEN** `get_agent_status` is called\n- **THEN** Kubernetes API SHALL raise `kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException` with status 404\n- **AND** the provider SHALL catch it and return `{\"status\": \"not_found\"}`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — delete agent\n\nThe system SHALL delete Deployment and Service resources.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful deletion\n\n- **GIVEN** a deployed agent\n- **WHEN** `delete_agent(agent_name)` is called\n- **THEN** the provider SHALL:\n  - Delete Deployment with `delete_namespaced_deployment`\n  - Delete Service with `delete_namespaced_service`\n  - Return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\": ..., \"namespace\": ...}`\n\n#### Scenario: Ignore 404 on deletion\n\n- **GIVEN** one or both resources do not exist\n- **WHEN** deletion API returns 404\n- **THEN** the provider SHALL ignore the error (treat as already deleted) and continue\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider initialization\n\nThe system SHALL construct `AgentCubeProvider` for AgentRuntime CR operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Default configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentCubeProvider` is instantiated\n- **WHEN** the constructor runs\n- **THEN** `namespace` SHALL default to `\"default\"`, `kubeconfig` to `None`, `verbose` to `False`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom namespace\n\n- **GIVEN** a specific namespace is required\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider(namespace=\"custom-ns\")` is instantiated\n- **THEN** all CR operations SHALL target that namespace\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider — deploy AgentRuntime CR\n\nThe system SHALL create or patch an `AgentRuntime` custom resource in group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`.\n\n#### Scenario: CR creation\n\n- **GIVEN** `deploy_agent_runtime(agent_name, image_url, port, entrypoint=None, env_vars=None, workload_manager_url=None, router_url=None, readiness_probe_path=None, readiness_probe_port=None)` is called\n- **WHEN** the CR is applied\n- **THEN** the provider SHALL:\n  - Sanitize agent name via `_sanitize_name`\n  - Ensure namespace exists\n  - Construct CR body with:\n    - `apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n    - `kind: AgentRuntime`\n    - `metadata.name`, `metadata.namespace`\n    - `spec.image`, `spec.port`\n    - `spec.command` if entrypoint provided\n    - `spec.env` from env_vars (plus `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL` if not in env_vars)\n    - `spec.sessionTimeout: \"15m\"`, `spec.maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"`\n    - `spec.imagePullSecrets: [{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n    - `spec.readinessProbe` if probe path/port provided\n  - Create via CustomObjectsApi `create_namespaced_custom_object`\n  - Return dict with `cr_name`, `namespace`, `status`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager URL injection\n\n- **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` is provided and not in `env_vars`\n- **WHEN** the CR spec is constructed\n- **THEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` SHALL be added to `spec.env`\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL injection\n\n- **GIVEN** `router_url` is provided and not in `env_vars`\n- **WHEN** the CR spec is constructed\n- **THEN** `ROUTER_URL` SHALL be added to `spec.env`\n\n#### Scenario: Readiness probe configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** `readiness_probe_path` and `readiness_probe_port` are provided\n- **WHEN** the CR spec is constructed\n- **THEN** `spec.readinessProbe` SHALL include:\n  - `httpGet.path: {readiness_probe_path}`\n  - `httpGet.port: {readiness_probe_port}`\n  - `initialDelaySeconds: 5`\n  - `periodSeconds: 10`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider — get AgentRuntime CR\n\nThe system SHALL retrieve the AgentRuntime CR and its status.\n\n#### Scenario: CR retrieval\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR exists\n- **WHEN** `get_agent_runtime(name, namespace)` is called\n- **THEN** the provider SHALL use `get_namespaced_custom_object` with:\n  - `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`\n  - `version=\"v1alpha1\"`\n  - `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`\n  - `namespace`, `name`\n  - Return the full CR dict or `None` if not found\n\n#### Scenario: CR not found\n\n- **GIVEN** no AgentRuntime CR exists for the name\n- **WHEN** `get_agent_runtime` is called\n- **THEN** the API SHALL raise 404\n- **AND** the provider SHALL catch and return `None`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CLI publish — provider selection\n\nThe system SHALL route publish operations to `AgentCubeProvider` or `KubernetesProvider` based on `--provider` option.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentCube provider publish\n\n- **GIVEN** `--provider agentcube` is specified\n- **WHEN** `publish` command runs\n- **THEN** `PublishRuntime` SHALL:\n  - Validate `metadata.router_url` and `metadata.workload_manager_url` are set (raise `ValueError` if missing)\n  - Call `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime`\n  - Update metadata with `k8s_deployment: {\"type\": \"AgentRuntime\", \"cr_name\": ..., \"namespace\": ...}`\n\n#### Scenario: K8s provider publish\n\n- **GIVEN** `--provider k8s` is specified\n- **WHEN** `publish` command runs\n- **THEN** `PublishRuntime` SHALL:\n  - Call `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`\n  - Call `wait_for_deployment_ready(timeout=120)`\n  - Update metadata with `k8s_deployment: {\"type\": \"Deployment\", \"deployment_name\": ..., \"service_name\": ..., \"namespace\": ..., \"node_port\": ...}`\n  - Raise `RuntimeError` on readiness timeout, recording error in metadata\n\n#### Scenario: Provider default\n\n- **GIVEN** `--provider` is omitted\n- **WHEN** `publish` runs\n- **THEN** `provider` SHALL default to `\"agentcube\"`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CLI invoke — provider-aware endpoint resolution\n\nThe system SHALL resolve invocation endpoint based on deployment type in metadata.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime invocation URL\n\n- **GIVEN** `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs with `provider=\"agentcube\"`\n- **THEN** the endpoint SHALL be constructed as:\n  - `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario: K8s Deployment invocation URL\n\n- **GIVEN** `k8s_deployment.type == \"Deployment\"`\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs with `provider=\"k8s\"`\n- **THEN** the endpoint SHALL be `http://localhost:{node_port}` from `k8s_deployment.node_port`\n\n#### Scenario: Direct HTTP invocation for K8s\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider=\"k8s\"` and endpoint is a direct HTTP URL\n- **WHEN** `_direct_http_invocation` runs\n- **THEN** the runtime SHALL `POST` JSON payload to the endpoint with custom headers\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CLI status — provider-aware status retrieval\n\nThe system SHALL retrieve status based on deployment type.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR status\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider=\"agentcube\"` and `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n- **THEN** status SHALL be:\n  - `cr_object[\"status\"][\"status\"]` if present\n  - `{\"status\": \"created_no_status\", \"agentEndpoint\": cr[\"status\"][\"agentEndpoint\"]}` if CR exists but status field missing\n  - `{\"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\"}` if CR does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: K8s Deployment status\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider=\"k8s\"` and `k8s_deployment.type == \"Deployment\"`\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status` runs\n- **THEN** status SHALL come from `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status`\n\n#### Scenario: Not published status\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.agent_id` is `None`\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"status\": \"not_published\"}`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CLI status — exit codes\n\nThe system SHALL exit with code 1 for non-ready states.\n\n#### Scenario: Not published exit\n\n- **GIVEN** status is `\"not_published\"`\n- **WHEN** `status` command prints output\n- **THEN** CLI SHALL print guidance message and exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: Error status exit\n\n- **GIVEN** status is `\"error\"`\n- **WHEN** `status` command completes\n- **THEN** CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Session header consistency\n\nThe system SHALL use consistent session header naming across providers and SDK.\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke session header\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.session_id` exists\n- **WHEN** HTTP invocation is performed\n- **THEN** request SHALL include header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` (uppercase X, capitalized Session, Id)\n\n#### Scenario: Header response handling\n\n- **GIVEN** a response contains session header\n- **WHEN** the response is processed\n- **THEN** the runtime SHALL read `x-agentcube-session-id` (lowercase) from response headers\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Error handling for provider operations\n\nThe system SHALL handle Kubernetes API exceptions gracefully.\n\n#### Scenario: API exception in verbose mode\n\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API exception occurs and `verbose=True`\n- **WHEN** `_handle_error` is called\n- **THEN** CLI SHALL print `Error {command}: {exception}` in red and full traceback, then exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: Missing Kubernetes dependency\n\n- **GIVEN** `kubernetes` package is not installed\n- **WHEN** provider classes are imported\n- **THEN** import SHALL fail or be caught, and CLI SHALL print message suggesting `pip install agentcube[k8s]`\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` class |\n| `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` class |\n| `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s`, `_publish_cr_to_k8s` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube`, `_direct_http_invocation` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status`, `_get_cr_k8s_status` |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `kubernetes>=28.0.0` | K8s API client, CustomObjectsApi |\n| `httpx>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for invocation |\n| `pydantic>=2.0.0` | Metadata model |\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] `KubernetesProvider.__init__` with namespace, kubeconfig, verbose params\n- [ ] `KubernetesProvider._ensure_namespace` creates namespace if missing\n- [ ] `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` creates Deployment + NodePort Service\n- [ ] `KubernetesProvider._sanitize_name` produces DNS-compliant names\n- [ ] `KubernetesProvider.wait_for_deployment_ready` polls with timeout\n- [ ] `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status` returns running/pending/not_found\n- [ ] `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent` removes resources, ignores 404\n- [ ] `AgentCubeProvider.__init__` with namespace, kubeconfig, verbose params\n- [ ] `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` creates AgentRuntime CR\n- [ ] `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime` retrieves CR or returns None\n- [ ] `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s` uses KubernetesProvider\n- [ ] `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s` uses AgentCubeProvider\n- [ ] `InvokeRuntime` resolves endpoint based on k8s_deployment.type\n- [ ] `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status` for Deployment type\n- [ ] `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` for AgentRuntime type\n- [ ] CLI status exits with code 1 for not_published/error"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775878037546,"end":1775878037623}}}}
